    "body": "@webprokopenko your options are out of order.\r\n```--rpcapi --rpcaddr \"0.0.0.0\" db,eth,net,web3,personal```\r\nshould be\r\n```--rpc --rpcaddr \"0.0.0.0\" --rpcapi db,eth,net,web3,personal```\r\n\r\nThe rpcapi list must have been interpretted as a positional argument and geth didn't complain. I wonder if that is a bug or if there's a good reason for it?",
